{"step_by_step_thinking": "Vitreous humor is the clear gel that fills the space between the lens and the retina of the eyeball. It is known to have a higher concentration of certain substances compared to blood. Sodium and glucose are typically higher in blood than in vitreous humor. Potassium levels are similar in both. However, ascorbate, also known as vitamin C, is known to be present in higher concentrations in the vitreous humor compared to blood.", "answer_choice": "D. Ascorbate"}
